nbtrain.py - Naive Bayes trainer
--------------------------------------------------------

- Requires python 3.2
- To run the program 
	nbtrain.py <training-directory> <model-file>
	Example: python nbtrain.py textcat\train\ mymodel
- The model is saved in the given <model-file>
- There will be a output of Top 20 terms with pos/neg weight and negative/positive weight in the console.


nbtest.py
---------------------------------------------------------

- Requires python 3.2
- To run the program 
	nbtest.py <model-file> <test-directory> <predictions-file>
	> python nbtest.py mymodel \textcat\dev prediction
- The result will be stored in the a <predictions-file>.csv file in the asked format


The results are stored in a csv file.
The top 20 terms for this trail can be found in Top20.txt

- The prediction file for test data is available as prediction_test.csv

